o leave as a couple or remain in the villa but stay single. They decided to stay, meaning they were not permitted to couple up during the next recoupling. However, during the recoupling both refused to couple with anybody else meaning they had to leave the villa.\n</small>\n\n==Casa Amor==\nOn 27 June 2017, it was confirmed that \u2018Casa Amor\u2019 would be reintroduced following its success during the previous series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/new-love-island-boys-girls-12803716|title=Meet the 12 new Love Island boys and girls|first=Rose|last=Hill|date=5 July 2018}}</ref> It is a second villa featuring new Islanders in a twist designed to put the couples to the ultimate test. Twelve new Islanders were introduced during this twist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-06-27/love-island-2018-12-new-cast-islanders-joining-itv2-show/|title=Meet the 12 new islanders set to cause chaos in Love Island}}</ref> The villa was called \u2019Casa Amor\u2019 which translates to \u2019Love House\u2019, and is located not far from the main villa. The new Islanders for the twist included six girls; Charlie, Darylle, Ellie, Grace, Kazimir and Savanna, as well as six boys; Alex, Charlie, Dean, Frankie, Jack and Jordan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/news/g25316/love-island-2018-meet-new-islanders-second-villa/|title=Meet all the NEW singletons moving into Love Island|date=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe twist came to its conclusion four days later when the original Islanders were given the choice of remaining with their current partner in the opposite villa or couple up with one of the new Islanders. However, as they were living in separate villas, they were not aware of each other's choice. If one decided to re-couple and the other did not, then the one that didn't would be single but still remain on the island. If both re-coupled then they would both remain in the villa with their new partner, and any remaining single new islanders would be dumped. At the end of this, Georgia and Wes became the only single original Islanders, and Charlie W, Dean, Jordan and Savanna were dumped.<ref name=\"digitalspy.com1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a860799/love-island-2018-catch-up-dumped-evicted-islanders-casa-amor-recoupling/|title=FOUR dumped from Love Island villa in Casa Amor twist|date=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Weekly summary==\nThe main events in the ''Love Island'' villa are summarised in the table below.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 96%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 1\n| '''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 1, Adam, Alex G, Dani, Eyal, Hayley, Jack Fi, Kendall, Laura A, Niall, Samira and Wes entered the villa.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hegarty |first1=Tasha |last2=Hutchinson |first2=Emily |title=See the Love Island girls and boys arriving at the villa in first-look pictures |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/news/g25276/love-island-contestants-girls-boys-villa-first-look-pictures/ |accessdate=6 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 4, Georgia and Rosie entered the villa.<ref name=\"Harp\"/>\n|-\n| '''Coupling''' ||\n* On Day 1, the Islanders coupled up for the first time. After all of the girls entered, the boys were asked to choose a girl to pair up with. Alex G was paired with Samira, Jack Fi with Dani, Eyal and Hayley paired up, Wes and Laura A coupled up, and Niall paired up with Kendall.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Harp |first1=Justin |title=Love Island 2018's first couplings are revealed \u2014 but there's already a twist to break one up |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a858737/love-island-2018-first-couples-revealed/ |accessdate=6 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 2, single Adam was given the opportunity to steal one of the girls. He chose Kendall, leaving Niall single.<ref name=\"Freedman\"/>\n* On Day 6, the islanders re-coupled. This time it was the boys who had to pick a girl to pair up with. Alex G and Samira, Dani and Jack Fi, Eyal and Hayley, and Laura A and Wes all remained together, and Adam chose to be with Rosie, and Niall coupled up with Georgia. As Kendall remained single, she was dumped from the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/363599-love-island-2018-results-who-left-one-girl-is-out-after-first-recoupling.html|title=Love Island 2018 results! One girl is out after first recoupling|date=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n||'''Dates''' ||\n* On Day 2, Adam and Kendall left the villa to go on a date.<ref name=\"Freedman\">{{cite news |last1=Freedman |first1=Joanna |title=Love Island 2018: Viewers fuming as Adam Collard chooses Kendall Rae-Knight in shock recoupling leaving Niall Aslam single \u2013 and they share a kiss |url=https://www.ok.co.uk/tv/love-island/1389888/love-island-2018-recoupling-kendall-rae-knight-niall-aslam-adam-collard-kiss-shock |accessdate=6 June 2018 |work=[[OK!]] |date=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 4, following a public vote for which boys to send on a date with new Islanders Georgia and Rosie. Niall was sent on a date with Georgia, and Alex G was chosen to date Rosie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/363215-love-island-2018-new-girls-georgia-steel-and-rosie-williams-make-their-entrance.html|title=Love Island's new girls Georgia Steel and Rosie Williams make their entrance|date=6 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 3, the girls and the boys competed against each other in \"Excess Baggage\" to guess which islander some facts are about. To make their guess they had to kiss that islander. The boys won the challenge by getting the most correct.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Starkey |first1=Adam |title=Love Island couples air their Excess Baggage in awkward first challenge |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/06/05/love-island-couples-air-excess-baggage-awkward-first-challenge-7608187/ |accessdate=6 June 2018 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 5, in a superhero themed challenge, the girls competed against each other to prove who had the biggest superpower. Kendall was the overall winner of the challenge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/363453-love-island-girls-crush-watermelons-with-their-bums-in-latest-task.html|title=Love Island girls crush watermelons with their bums in latest task|date=7 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 6, Kendall was dumped from the island after failing to couple up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a859097/love-island-2018-recoupling-kendall-elimination-three-new-islanders-coming/|title=Love Island's first singleton dumped from the villa|date=8 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 2\n| '''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 8, Charlie F, Josh D and Megan entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a859147/love-island-megan-josh-charlie-bombshells/|title=Get to know the three new Love Island contestants|date=9 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Coupling''' ||\n* On Day 10, the islanders re-coupled. This time it was the girls who had to pick a boy to couple up with. Adam and Rosie, Alex G and Samira, Dani and Jack Fi, Wes and Laura A all remained together, and Georgia chose to be with Josh D, Megan coupled up with Eyal, and Hayley picked Charlie F.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/364078-love-island-2018-results-recoupling-revealed-as-villa-gets-a-shake-up.html|title=Love Island 2018 results! Recoupling revealed as villa gets a shake up|date=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Dates''' ||\n* On Day 7, Dani and Jack Fi left the villa to go on a date.\n* On Day 8, new Islanders Charlie F, Josh D and Megan were asked to choose three other Islanders to take on dates. Charlie F chose Hayley, Samira and Georgia, Josh D picked Hayley, Samira and Laura A, and Megan chose Alex G, Eyal and Niall.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/363801-love-island-spoiler-georgia-steel-fuming-at-new-girl-megan-barton-hanson.html|title=Love Island: Georgia Steel \"fuming\" at new girl Megan Barton Hanson|date=11 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 11, after winning a challenge, Wes and Laura A were rewarded with a date.\n* On Day 13, Georgia and Josh D left the villa to go on a date.\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 11, the couples took part in \"Meals on Wheels\" where a three course meal had to be passed from the boy to the girl using their mouths alone. Wes and Laura A won the challenge by completing this in the quickest time.\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 9, Niall left the villa due to personal reasons.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\"/>\n* On Day 12, the Islanders voted anonymously for the two least compatible couples. As Alex G and Samira, and Charlie F and Hayley received the most votes they then went head-to-head in a public vote to save. On Day 13, Charlie F and Hayley were dumped from the island having received the fewest votes.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 3\n| '''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 15, Ellie B and Zara entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a859667/love-island-ellie-zara-new-bombshells/|title=Check out the two bombshells entering Love Island villa|date=16 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 19, Sam entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/364797-love-island-2018-new-guy-sam-bird-set-to-stir-things-up-tonight.html|title=Love Island 2018: New guy Sam Bird set to stir things up|date=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Coupling''' ||\n*On Day 20, the islanders re-coupled. This time it was the boys who had to pick a girl to couple up with. Dani and Jack Fi, Laura A and Wes, Georgia and Josh D and Eyal and Megan all remained together, and Adam chose to be with new girl Zara, Alex G coupled up with Ellie B and new boy Sam chose Samira.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/364967-love-island-2018-recoupling-results-who-coupled-up-with-who-revealed.html|title=Love Island 2018 recoupling: Who coupled up with who revealed|date=22 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Dates''' ||\n*On Day 16, new Islanders Ellie B and Zara were asked to choose three other Islanders to take on dates. Ellie B chose Josh D, Wes and Alex G, and Zara chose Alex G, Eyal and Adam.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/364565-love-island-2018s-new-girls-go-dating-will-alex-finally-find-love.html|title=Love Island's new girls go dating \u2013 will Alex G finally find love?|date=18 June 2018}}</ref>\n*On Day 19, Eyal and Megan left the villa to go on a date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/love-island-fans-cringe-eyal-12763804|title=Love Island fans cringe as Eyal makes bizarre confession|first=Rose|last=Hill|date=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n*On Day 20, new islander Sam was asked to choose three other Islanders to take on a date. He chose, Rosie, Samira and Ellie B.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pretty52.com/entertaining/tv-and-film-love-island-2018-first-look-gives-glimpse-of-tonights-recoupling-20180622|title=Love Island 2018: Recoupling Turns Tense After Sam Bird Ruffles People's Feathers|date=22 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 18, the girls took part in \"Girls Night In\", where they were faced with a number of [[slumber party]] themed games.\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 20, Rosie was dumped from the island after failing to couple up.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/364913-love-island-2018-results-who-left-one-girl-dumped-from-the-villa.html|title=Love Island results! One girl DUMPED from the villa|date=22 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 4\n| '''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 26, Alex M, Charlie B, Dean, Frankie, Jack Fo and Jordan entered the villa, and Charlie W, Darylle, Ellie J, Grace, Kazimir and Savanna entered Casa Amor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/365339-love-island-2018-reveals-twelve-new-contestants-in-huge-new-twist-tonight.html|title=Love Island reveals TWELVE new contestants in huge new twist|date=28 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 22, the couples took part in a number of [[music festival]] themed games.\n* On Day 23, the Islanders took part in a quiz about their other half. The Islanders wrote down the answers to the questions, and if it matched their partner's then they'd score a point. Dani and Jack Fi won the challenge with the most points\n* On Day 24, the Islanders took part in a game of \"Snog, Marry, Pie\", where both the boys and girls were tasked with choosing an islander of the opposite gender, to snog, marry and pie, using wedding rings and pies.\n* On Day 27, the Islanders in the main villa went head-to-head again with the Islanders in Casa Amor, where they took part in a number of challenges. For every challenge won they would earn a point, where the villa with the most points at the end would receive a party.\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 25, after receiving the fewest public votes, Adam and Zara, Alex G and Ellie B, and Eyal and Megan were in danger of leaving. The remaining Islanders had to choose one boy and one girl to dump from the island. The boys chose Zara, and the girls chose Eyal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/365338-love-island-2018-results-who-left-two-islanders-kicked-out-of-the-villa.html|title=Love Island 2018 results! Two Islanders kicked out of the villa|date=27 June 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 26, Adam, Alex G, Jack Fi, Josh D, Sam and Wes moved out of the villa and moved into Casa Amor.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 5\n| '''Coupling''' ||\n* On Day 30, the original Islanders were told that they would be re-coupling. They were only given the option to remain in their current couple or to choose one of the new Islanders. However, as the boys and the girls were living in separate villas, they were not aware of what the other one chose. If one decided to re-couple and the other did not, then they would be single but still remain on the island. If both re-coupled then they would both remain in the villa with their new partner, and any remaining single new islanders would be dumped. Already single Adam chose Darylle, and Megan chose Alex M. Dani and Jack Fi stayed loyal, and Samira and Sam both decided to recouple with Frankie and Ellie J respectively, and Alex G and Ellie B chose Grace and Charlie B. Laura A chose Jack Fo, whereas Wes chose to remain single, and Josh D brought Kazimir to the villa leaving Georgia single.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/365878-love-island-2018-recoupling-results-revealed-whos-with-who.html|title=New Love Island recoupling results revealed: Who's with who|date=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 33, after the public voted for their favourite couple, it was announced that Adam & Darylle, Alex M & Megan, and Ellie J & Sam had the fewest votes. It was then down to the only single Islanders Georgia and Wes to couple up with one of them, and therefore save them from being dumped. Georgia chose to couple up with Sam, and Wes chose Megan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/366199-love-island-2018-latest-four-leave-in-results-as-villa-is-rocked-by-rows.html|title=Love Island latest! Four leave in results as villa is rocked by rows|date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Dates''' ||\n* On Day 33, as the only single Islanders, Georgia and Wes were given the opportunity to go on two dates. Georgia chose Jack Fo and Sam, and Wes chose Darylle and Megan.\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 31, the couples took part in \"Babewatch\", where they competed against each other in a number of beach themed challenges. Charlie B and Ellie B were the overall winners of the challenge.\n* On Day 34, the boys and the girls competed to get each other's hearts racing the most by performing sexy dances. The boys were the overall winners of this challenge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/366275-love-island-contestants-take-part-in-a-sexy-dance-off-challenge.html|title=Love Island contestants take part in a sexy dance off challenge|date=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 30, Charlie W, Dean, Jordan and Savanna were dumped from the island after failing to couple up.<ref name=\"digitalspy.com1\"/>\n* On Day 33, Adam, Alex M, Darylle and Ellie J were dumped after failing to be chosen by Georgia or Wes to be in a couple with them.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a861046/love-island-sends-four-islanders-home-mass-axing/|title=Love Island sends four Islanders home in mass axing|date=5 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 6\n| '''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 37, Idris and Kieran entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a861257/love-island-2018-new-islanders-kieran-nicholls-idris-virgo/|title=Meet the two new boys heading to Love Island|date=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 39, Alexandra entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/366659-love-island-2018-meet-new-girl-alexandra-cane-who-wants-to-date-dr-alex.html|title=Love Island: Meet new girl Alexandra Cane \u2013 who wants to date Dr Alex|date=11 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Dates''' ||\n* On Day 37, Josh D and Kazimir left the villa to go on a date.\n* On Day 38, new Islanders Idris and Kieran were asked to choose another Islander to take on a date. Idris chose Laura A, and Kieran picked Georgia.\n* On Day 39, before entering the villa, new Islander Alexandra went on dates with both Alex and Jack Fo.\n|-\n| '''Coupling''' ||\n* On Day 40, the Islanders recoupled, this time with the girls choosing which boy they'd like to couple up with. Dani and Jack Fi, Laura A and Jack Fo, Georgia and Sam, Megan and Wes, Ellie B and Charlie B, and Kazimir and Josh D all remained together, and Alexandra coupled up with Alex G for the first time. This left Idris and Kieran single, who were subsequently dumped from the island.<ref name=\"tellymix.co.uk3\">{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/366868-love-island-2018-results-who-left-two-boys-dumped-after-recoupling.html|title=Love Island 2018 results! Two boys dumped after recoupling|date=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 40, the boys took part in a sexy rescue mission. Dressed as a fireman, they had to perform a strip tease, endure a number of obstacles and rescue a cat from a tree for the girl they're coupled with. Idris was chosen as the winner of this challenge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/366767-love-island-2018-contestants-get-hot-and-sweaty-in-tonights-challenge.html|title=Love Island contestants get hot and sweaty in tonight's challenge|date=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 41, the couples played \"[[Twitter]] Bingo\" where they took part in a quiz based on viewers opinions. \n|-\n| '''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 37, the public voted for their favourite boy and girl. As Frankie and Grace received the fewest votes, they were dumped from the island.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a861261/love-island-cast-2018-jack-dani-dumped-islanders-grace-frankie/|title=Love Island dumps two more islanders in shock reshuffle|date=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 40, Samira voluntarily left the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a861457/love-island-2018-samira-mighty-leaves-quits-show/|title=Love Island's Samira walks out of villa|date=12 July 2018}}</ref> On the same day, after failing to re-couple, Idris and Kieran were dumped from the island.<ref name=\"tellymix.co.uk3\"/>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 7\n|'''Entrances''' ||\n* On Day 43, Josh M, Laura C, Paul and Stephanie entered the villa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367142-love-island-2018-latest-one-couple-dumped-four-newbies-and-a-big-twist.html|title=Love Island 2018 latest! One couple dumped, four newbies and a big twist|date=16 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Dates''' ||\n* On Day 47 as a result of winning the challenge Jack Fo and Laura C left the villa to go on a date.\n|-\n|'''Challenges'''||\n* On Day 42, the couples took part in a quiz guessing who came top of a public poll about them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367024-love-island-2018-couples-find-out-what-viewers-really-think-of-them-in-new-task.html|title=Love Island couples find out what fans REALLY think of them in new task|date=15 July 2018}}</ref>\n*On Day 47, the couples took part in 'Master Baker' where the boys were blindfolded and attached to the girl's body and they had to decorate a cake.  Jack Fo and Laura C won the challenge.\n|-\n|'''Coupling''' ||\n* On Day 47, the Islanders recoupled, this time with the boys choosing which girl they'd like to couple up with. As Sam and Georgia had previously decided to remain in the villa apart, they were not permitted to choose each other. However, they refused to recouple. As a result of this, they were dumped from the island. Elsewhere, Dani and Jack Fi, Megan and Wes and Kazimir and Josh D, Alexandra and Alex G all remained together while Josh M coupled up with Stephanie, Jack Fo chose to couple up with Laura C and Paul chose to couple up with Laura A.\n|-\n|'''Exits'''||\n* On Day 43, the viewers voted for their favourite couples. As Charlie B and Ellie B received the fewest votes, they were dumped from the island.\n* On Day 47, Sam and Georgia were dumped from the island after refusing to recouple.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 8\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 50, the girls competed against each other in \"Ladies Day\" where they raced around a course on a horse space hopper. Laura C was the eventual winner of this challenge.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367744-love-island-2018-girls-go-head-to-head-in-strange-new-challenge.html|title=Love Island's girls go head to head in new challenge|date=22 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 51, the boys took a lie detector test with the girls asking the questions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367813-love-island-2018-spoilers-the-lie-detector-arrives-in-the-villa.html|title=Love Island 2018 spoilers: The lie detector arrives in the villa|date=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 52, the Islanders took part in \"Shake it Off\" where they were split into two teams and had to guess the missing words in various media headlines.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367910-love-island-2018-alexandra-cane-exposed-in-surprise-new-task.html|title=Love Island's Alexandra Cane exposed in surprise new task|date=24 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 53, the couples had their parenting skills tested by looking after dolls.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367931-love-island-2018-the-babies-arrive-in-the-villa-to-test-the-couples.html|title=Love Island: The babies arrive in the villa to test the couples|date=25 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|'''Dates'''||\n* On Day 50, Alex and Alexandra left the villa to go on a date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/367742-love-islands-alex-george-and-alexandra-cane-get-close-out-on-a-date.html|title=Love Island's Alex and Alexandra get close out on a date|date=22 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 54, Dani and Jack, Alex and Alexandra, and Laura and Paul left the villa to go on their final ''Love Island'' date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/368020-love-island-2018-spoiler-jack-has-a-big-question-for-dani-on-epic-hot-air-balloon-date.html|title=Love Island: Jack asks Dani to move in with him after epic date|date=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/368021-love-island-2018-trouble-for-alexandra-cane-and-alex-george-after-epic-date.html|title=Love Island: Trouble for Alexandra and Alex after epic date|date=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/love-island/368067-love-island-spoilers-laura-anderson-and-paul-knops-make-it-official.html|title=Love Island spoilers! Laura Anderson and Paul Knops make it official|date=26 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 55, Megan and Wes, and Kazimir and Josh left the villa to go on their final ''Love Island'' date.\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 50, Josh M and Stephanie were dumped from the island after receiving the fewest public votes to save.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a862188/tonights-dumped-love-island-couple-talk-exit/|title=Newly dumped Love Island couple speak out after exit|date=22 July 2018}}</ref>\n* On Day 53, Jack Fo and Laura C were dumped from the island after receiving the fewest public votes to save.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 6%;\" | Week 9\n|'''Challenges''' ||\n* On Day 59, as winners, Dani and Jack Fi were given the choice of two envelopes. One containing \u00a350,000 and the other containing nothing. As Jack Fi picked the one with the money in, he was given the choice to keep it for himself of split the money with Dani. He chose to share.\n|-\n|'''Exits''' ||\n* On Day 57, Alex G and Alexandra were dumped from the island having received the fewest public votes following the Islanders anonymous vote for the couple they wanted to dump. As Alex G and Alexandra, Josh D and Kazimir, and Laura A and Paul received the most votes they then went head-to-head in a public vote to save.\n* On Day 59, Megan and Wes left the villa in fourth place, and Kazimir and Josh D finished third. Dani and Jack Fi were then voted the winners, leaving Laura A and Paul as runners-up.\n|-\n|}\n\n==Ratings==\nOfficial ratings are taken from [[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board|BARB]] and include ITV2 +1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-10/|title=BARB \u2013 Weekly Top 30 Programmes: ITV2 Total|accessdate=28 December 2012}}</ref> Because the Saturday episodes are weekly catch-up episodes rather than nightly highlights, these are not included in the overall averages. The series launch on 4 June 2018 was the most watched digital TV programme since the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] were broadcast on [[BBC Three]], and the most watched ever on [[ITV2]], this was overtaken by the episode that aired on 8 July 2018 which had 4.46 million viewers.<ref name=\"ratings record\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/entertainment/first-episode-of-love-island-was-mostwatched-itv2-programme-ever-37005573.html|title=First episode of Love Island was most-watched ITV2 programme ever|last=Mapstone|first=Lucy|date=13 June 2018|work=[[Irish Independent]]|accessdate=13 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%; text-align:center; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12%;\"|\n! scope=col colspan=13| Viewers (millions)\n|-\n! Week 1\n! Week 2\n! Week 3\n! Week 4\n! Week 5\n! Week 6\n! Week 7\n! Week 8\n! Week 9\n|-\n! Sunday\n| bgcolor=\"#cccccc\" |  || 3.65 || 3.95 || 3.74 || 4.27 || 4.46 || 3.94 || 3.64 || 4.13\n|-\n! Monday\n| 4.05 || 3.76 || 3.86 || 3.56 || 4.17 || 4.17 || 4.01 || 4.07 || 4.32\n|-\n! Tuesday\n| 3.91 || 4.00 || 4.00 || 3.98 || 3.83 || 4.11 || 4.01 || 3.88 || bgcolor=\"#cccccc\" rowspan=\"4\" | \n|-\n! Wednesday\n| 3.81 || 3.88 || 4.04 || 4.09 || 3.97 || 4.03 || 3.79 || 3.82\n|-\n! Thursday\n| 3.63 || 3.87 || 3.71 || 4.36 || 4.31 || 3.75 || 3.89 || 3.84\n|-\n! Friday\n| 3.66 || 3.71 || 3.63 || 4.22 || 4.13 || 3.99 || 3.86 || 3.80\n|-\n! Weekly average\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.81\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.81\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.87\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.99\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 4.11\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 4.09\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.92\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 3.84\n| style=\"background:#FADADD;\" | 4.23\n|-\n! Running average\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.81\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.81\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.83\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.87\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.92\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.95\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.94\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.93\n| style=\"background:#EEDC82;\" | 3.96\n|-\n! Series average\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"background:#ADDFAD;\" | 3.96\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000\" colspan=\"10\"|\n|-\n! Weekly Hotlist\n| bgcolor=\"#cccccc\" rowspan=\"2\" |  || 1.09 || 0.88 || 1.09 || 1.23 || 0.86 || 0.89 || 0.73 || 0.89\n|-\n! ''Aftersun''\n| 1.40 || 1.66 || 1.41 || 1.86 || 2.18 || 1.59  || 1.59 || 1.71\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Love Island}}\n\n[[Category:ITV reality television programmes]]\n[[Category:2018 British television seasons]]\n[[Category:Love Island (2015 TV series)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Fourth series of Love Island}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| season_number    = 4\n| image            = \n| country          = United Kingdom\n| network          = [[ITV2]]\n| first_aired      = {{Start date|2018|6|4|df=y}}\n| last_aired       = {{End date|2018|7|30|df=y}}\n| num_episodes     = 49\n}}\nThe fourth series of ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]'', a British [[dating show|dating reality show]], began on 4 June 2018 on [[ITV2]], and concluded on 30 July 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a861866/love-island-final-2018-date/|title=The Love Island final date has been revealed|date=18 July 2018|work=Digital Spy}}</ref> It is the fourth from the current [[Love Island (2015 TV series)|revived series]], but sixth overall. [[Caroline Flack]] presented the series, while [[Iain Stirling]] narrated it. The series opener received the highest rating on a digital TV programme since the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] were broadcast on [[BBC Three]]; it was also the most watched programme ever on ITV2.\n\nOn 30 July 2018, the series was won by Dani Dyer and Jack Fincham having received 79.66% of the final vote, making this the biggest winning percentage since the show began.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/love-island-voting-figures-reveal-13009267|title=Love Island voting figures reveal exactly how much Dani and Jack won by|first=Vicki|last=Newman|date=31 July 2018|work=Daily Mirror}}</ref> Laura Anderson and Paul Knops finished as runners-up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a862765/love-island-2018-winners/|title=The Love Island 2018 winners are...|date=30 July 2018|work=Digital Spy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-44943562|title=Love Island: Dani Dyer and Jack Fincham win ITV2 series|date=31 July 2018|work=BBC News|accessdate=31 July 2018}}</ref> The average viewers for this series was 3.96 million,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-10/|title=Weekly top 10 programmes|publisher=BARB}}</ref> up 1.44 million on the previous series.\n\n==Production==\nDuring the final of the [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 3)|previous series]] on 24 July 2017, it was confirmed that ''Love Island'' would return for a fourth series due to air the following year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Duncan |first1=Amy |title=Love Island series 4 confirmed \u2013 but we have to wait a whole year for it |url=https://metro.co.uk/2017/07/24/love-island-series-4-confirmed-but-we-have-to-wait-a-whole-year-for-it-6803071/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |date=24 July 2017}}</ref> It becomes the fourth series from the current [[Love Island (2015 TV series)|revived format]], but sixth series overall.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a641877/caroline-flack-confirmed-to-present-new-look-love-island-on-itv2/|title=Caroline Flack fronts new-look Love Island|last=Rigby|first=Sam|date=15 April 2015|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]]|accessdate=4 July 2017}}</ref> [[Caroline Flack]] and [[Iain Stirling]] were confirmed to continue their roles as presenter and narrator, respectively.<ref name=\"Agius\">{{cite news |last1=Agius |first1=Nicola |last2=Guiltenane |first2=Christian |title=Love Island 2018: When it starts, line-up and everything else you need to know |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/feature/a847317/love-island-2018-cast-date-contestants/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=23 May 2018}}</ref> The first 10-second teaser for the new series began airing on 21 April 2018 with a second teaser released on 29 April.<ref name=\"Trailer\">{{cite news |last1=Houghton |first1=Rianne |title=Updated: Love Island 2018 is officially almost here as ITV2 drops another teaser |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a855349/love-island-start-date-2018-itv2-first-teaser-trailer/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=29 April 2018}}</ref> A full length trailer was released on 17 May, which Stephanie Chase of ''[[Digital Spy]]'' pointed out included \"all our favourite lingo from the show\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chase |first1=Stephanie |title=Love Island series 4's latest trailer includes every possible reference to show's cheeky lingo |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a857314/love-island-series-four-trailer-lingo/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=17 May 2018}}</ref> On 23 May, it was confirmed that the series would begin on 4 June on [[ITV2]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCreesh |first1=Louise |title=Love Island 2018 bags an official launch date, and it's really soon |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a857857/love-island-2018-start-date-itv2-launch-premiere/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=23 May 2018}}</ref> On 27 May, it was announced that a new spin-off, \"''Love Island: The Morning After''\", had been commissioned for the series. It is hosted by [[Kem Cetinay]] and Arielle Free and is a daily podcast delivering the freshest gossip to the fans.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Houghton |first1=Rianne |title=Love Island star Kem Cetinay is presenting a new podcast about the show |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a858124/love-island-season-4-kem-cetinay-podcast-host/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=27 May 2018}}</ref> First look pictures of the villa were released on 31 May.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Harman |first1=Abi |title=Love Island 2018: First look at the lush new villa |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/reality-tv/news/g25271/love-island-2018-first-look-at-the-new-villa/?slide=8 |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=31 May 2018}}</ref> The sixteenth episode of the series, first broadcast on 21 June 2018, features a tribute to [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 2)|series 2]] contestant [[Sophie Gradon]], who died on 20 June.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Harp |first1=Justin |title=Love Island pays on-air tribute to Sophie Gradon hours after her tragic death |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/love-island/news/a860016/love-island-tribute-sophie-gradon-after-death/ |accessdate=21 June 2018 |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines UK]] |date=21 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nSome episodes this series were aired outside of the usual 9pm timeslot due to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>https://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/a21983893/love-island-time-change-teaser/</ref>\n\n==Islanders==\nAngela Jain, the managing director at ITV Studios Entertainment, wanted the series to feature \"some surprising cast members\", who the audience would not expect to see.<ref name=\"Taylor\">{{cite news |last1=Taylor |first1=Frances |title=Love Island producers tease \"genuinely surprising\" cast for 2018 series |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-05-25/love-island-producers-tease-genuinely-surprising-cast-for-2018-series/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Radio Times]] |date=25 May 2018}}</ref> She explained that she wanted \"enough cast that feels like they are absolutely heart and soul ''Love Island'' \u2013 and then a certain percentage of people who feel genuinely new to telly and genuinely surprising.\"<ref name=\"Taylor\"/> When asked whether a former contestant could appear in this series, executive producer Andy Cadman did not rule out anything, but said he struggled to imagine it.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Harrison |first1=Ellie |title=Could Love Island put a 2017 contestant back in the villa? |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2018-06-01/could-love-island-put-a-2017-contestant-back-in-the-villa/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Radio Times]] |date=1 June 2018}}</ref> The first Islanders for the fourth series were released on 28 May 2018, just one week before the launch.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Taylor |first1=Frances |title=Who's going to be in the new series of Love Island? |url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-06-02/love-island-2018-cast-contestants-list-and-rumours-full-confirmed-line-up-revealed/ |accessdate=3 June 2018 |work=[[Radio Times]] |date=2 June 2018}}</ref> However, throughout the series, more Islanders entered the villa to find love.<ref name=\"Harp\"/> Niall Aslam's decision to leave the series voluntarily for \"personal reasons\" marks the first time since the [[Love Island (2015 TV series, series 2)|second series]] where an Islander voluntarily left the show.<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-44457713|title=Niall quits the Love Island villa|date=12 June 2018|via=www.bbc.co.uk|work=BBC News}}</ref> The series was won by Dani Dyer and Jack Fincham having received 79.66% of the final vote.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! width=\"150\"|'''Islander'''\n! width=\"50\"|'''Age'''\n! width=\"120\"|'''Hometown'''\n! width=\"50\"|'''Entered'''\n! width=\"150\"|'''Status'''\n! width=\"50\"|'''{{abbr|Ref|Reference}}'''\n|-\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''Dani Dyer'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''21'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''[[London]]'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''Day 1'''\n| style=\"background:gold;\"| '''Winner (Day 59)'''\n| <ref>{{cite news|last1=Waring|first1=Olivia|title=Meet Love Island 2018 contestant Dani Dyer \u2013 daughter of actor Danny Dyer|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/05/28/meet-love-island-2018-contestant-dani-dyer-daughter-of-actor-danny-dyer-7583423/|accessdate=3 June 2018|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|date=28 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''Jack Fincham'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''26'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''[[Kent]]'''\n| style=\"background:lavender;\"| '''Day 1'''\n| style=\"background:gold;\"| '''Winner (Day 59)'''\n| <ref>{{cite news|last1=Waring|first1=Olivia|title=Meet Love Island 2018 contestant Jack Fincham, a stationary salesman from Kent|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/05/28/meet-love-island-2018-contestant-jack-fincham-a-stationary-salesman-from-kent-7584593/|accessdate=3 June 2018|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|date=28 May 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| Laura Anderson\n| 29\n| [[Stirling]]\n| Day 1\n| style=\"background:silver;\"| R